 * 1. `@.arguments` - This iterator searches for the first node named `.arguments` within the current context. It is typically used to access the arguments node in a Hyperlambda file or endpoint, which contains the parameters passed to a function or endpoint.
 * 
 * 2. `*` - This iterator retrieves all children nodes of the `.arguments` node. It is used to access each argument passed to the function or endpoint.
